SIMPLE: queasy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Queasy
<hw>Quea"sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Icel.
<ets>kweisa</ets> pain; cf. Norw. <ets>kveis</ets> sickness after a
debauch.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sick at the stomach; affected with
nausea; inclined to vomit; qualmish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fastidious; squeamish; delicate; easily disturbed;
unsettled; ticklish.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>queasy</xex> question.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some seek, when <qex>queasy</qex> conscience has its qualms.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quebec group</ent>⟦br⟧
